    "the company and the ethics board could be two separate legal entities.",
    "The relationship between the two entities is typically governed by a contract.The separate legal entity could be a nonprofit organization (e.g.",
    "a 501(c)(3)) or a for-profit company (e.g.",
    "a public-benefit corporation [PBC]).",
    "The individuals who provide services to the company could be members of the board of directors of the ethics board (Fig. 1a)."
